- The class has @Path("/api/v0") and the method has @Path("/probes/liveness"), so the full route is the concatenation: /api/v0/probes/liveness.

- The method also declares @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_PLAIN) and returns "OK" with Response.ok(...), but that affects content type and response body, not allowed HTTP methods.
